# Optional: Go module download settings for docker image builds.
# Useful in restricted networks (corporate proxy, blocked sumdb, etc.).
#
# Common fixes:
# - If the Go proxy is flaky/unreachable, prefer the pipe form so Go falls back
#   to direct VCS fetches on *any* proxy error (comma only falls back on 404/410):
#   GOPROXY=https://proxy.golang.org|direct
# - If proxy.golang.org is blocked but GitHub is reachable:
#   GOPROXY=direct
# - If sum.golang.org is blocked:
#   GOSUMDB=off
# - For fully-offline builds (after `go mod vendor` in ./server):
#   SC_USE_VENDOR=1
# - If module downloads fail during image build due to DNS/egress issues inside the
#   build sandbox (common in some Portainer/remote builder environments), try:
#   SC_BUILD_NETWORK=host
# - If the builder injects a broken DNS server and you cannot use host networking,
#   you can override resolv.conf inside the build container:
#   SC_BUILD_DNS="1.1.1.1 8.8.8.8"
#
# GOPROXY=https://proxy.golang.org|direct
# GOSUMDB=sum.golang.org
# GOPRIVATE=
# GONOSUMDB=
# SC_USE_VENDOR=0
# SC_BUILD_NETWORK=default
# SC_BUILD_DNS=
